<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - INSTALL - MAIN DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>MAIN DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mark the main drive gear for timing purposes. Mark any two adjacent teeth on the drive gear
                and repeat the procedure for the two adjacent teeth directly opposite the first set marked (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021i4">Figure 184</hotlnk>). A highly visible color of toolmaker's dye is recommended
                for making timing marks.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021i4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021i4" filename="../figg13/G13021i4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 184. Mark Main Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mesh the marked tooth of the left countershaft drive gear with the two marked teeth on the
                main drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021i5">Figure 185</hotlnk>). Slide the input shaft through the main drive gear.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021i5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021i5" filename="../figg13/G13021i5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 185. Input Shaft Through Main Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the spacer and the bearing on the input shaft with the external snap ring to the
                outside (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021i6">Figure 186</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021i6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021i6" filename="../figg13/G13021i6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 186. Install Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the bearing into the bore with a suitable driver (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021i7">Figure 187</hotlnk>). Temporarily install the front bearing cover and drive
                the input shaft into the bearing from the rear.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021i7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021i7" filename="../figg13/G13021i7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 187. Install Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
